# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Nonogram — git ignore rules
#
# Nonogram is a 1993-97 16-bit Borland TPW 1.5 OWL puzzle app being rebuilt as a
# native 32-bit PE with the mdtpw toolchain. The original sources (NONOGRAM.PAS,
# NONOGRAM.RES) and the historical 1990s binaries (NONOGRAM.EXE, RELEASE/) stay
# tracked; everything the build *derives*, plus local scratch, is not.
#
# NOT ignored (tracked on purpose): generated/  (the reconstructed Win32 .rc +
# bmp/ico assets — a build *input* referenced by mdtpw.toml, not an output) and
# _puzzles/ (the bundled .NGM puzzle library).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- mdtpw build output (Pascal -> LLVM IR -> COFF -> linked PE32 + .res) ---
/target/
/.mdtpw-imports/
*.ll
*.obj
# The build EXE is deliberately suffixed so it never clobbers the tracked 1990s
# 16-bit NONOGRAM.EXE (see mdtpw.toml `output`). The lowercase `nonogram.exe` is
# also ignored defensively: on case-insensitive Windows it aliases the tracked
# NONOGRAM.EXE, so a stray build with that name can never re-track/clobber it.
nonogram_mdtpw.exe
nonogram.exe

# --- scratch working copies of the source (canonical source is NONOGRAM.PAS) ---
nonogram.pas.orig
nonogram_work.pas
nonogram_survey.pas

# --- backup of the original 16-bit resource (NONOGRAM.RES is the tracked one) ---
NONOGRAM.RES.orig16

# --- runtime config written by the app at exit ---
NONOGRAM.INI

# --- build / survey logs ---
*.log
build_log.txt
survey_log.txt

# --- scratch working directories ---
# _diag/   : solver probes, FOR-var/codegen test programs, throwaway binaries
# _survey/ : read-only copies of nonogram.pas + mdtpw runtime_pas for surveying
# shots/   : PrintWindow capture scratch from the headless verification scripts
/_diag/
/_survey/
/shots/
